headlines.description: — Brandon Miller scored 26 points, Tre Mann added 21 points, eight rebounds and six assists, and the Charlotte Hornets won their season-high third straight game, 122-99 over the Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Miller, Tre Mann lead Hornets past Hawks 122-99 for season-high third straight win

events.name: New York Knicks at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 36 points, Franz Wagner added 21 and the Orlando Magic beat the injury-riddled New York Knicks 118-100 on Wednesday night in the final game before the All-Star break for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero scores 36 points, Magic beat injury-riddled Knicks 118-100

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 23 points and 14 rebounds to help the Miami Heat beat the Philadelphia 76ers 109-104 on Wednesday night in the final game for both teams before the NBA All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo has 23 points and 14 rebounds in Heat's 109-104 victory over 76ers

headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard scored 28 points and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics routed Brooklyn 136-86 on Wednesday night, giving Joe Mazzulla his 100th victory as head coach and handing the Nets the second-worst loss in franchise history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics cruise past Nets 136-86 to give Joe Mazzulla his 100th win as head coach

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 30 points, including the go-ahead free throw with 44 seconds left, and the Cleveland Cavaliers overcame a 17-point deficit to beat the Chicago Bulls 108-105 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 30 points, Cavaliers rally from 17 down to beat Bulls 108-105

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 21 points and 12 assists, Pascal Siakam scored 23 against his former team and the Indiana Pacers beat the Toronto Raptors 127-125 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 23 against former team as Pacers beat Raptors 127-125 heading into All-Star break

headlines.description: — GG Jackson scored 20 points, Jaren Jackson Jr. had 18, including 11 in the fourth quarter, and the Memphis Grizzlies ended their nine-game losing streak with a 121-113 victory over the Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: GG Jackson has 20, Jaren Jackson adds 18 as Grizzlies snap skid with 121-113 win over Rockets.

events.name: Washington Wizards at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 36 points, CJ McCollum added 26 and the New Orleans Pelicans beat Washington 133-126 on Wednesday night, overcoming Deni Avdija's career-best 43 points for the Wizards.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson leads Pelicans past Wizards 133-126 on career night for Washington's Deni Avdija

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 34 points, Luka Doncic had 27 before leaving early in the fourth period and the Dallas Mavericks overcame an early 15-point deficit to beat the San Antonio Spurs 116-93 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving and Doncic lead Mavericks past Wenbanyama and Spurs, 116-93

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had 30 points, eight assists and eight rebounds, Domantas Sabonis had 20 points and 13 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings rallied from a 16-point, second-half deficit to beat the Denver Nuggets 102-98 Wednesday night in the final game...
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores 30 points, rallies Kings from 16 down for 102-98 victory over Nuggets

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 25 points and the Phoenix Suns overcame fellow All-Star Devin Booker's early ejection to rout Detroit 116-100 on Wednesday night in Pistons coach Monty Williams first game in Phoenix since being fired by the Suns.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns shake off Booker's early ejection, roll past Pistons 116-100

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 37 points and 15 rebounds and Rui Hachimura scored a career-high 36 points for the Los Angeles Lakers, who beat the Utah Jazz 138-122 on Wednesday night while resting LeBron James in their final game before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Davis, Rui Hachimura lead Lakers past Jazz 138-122 with LeBron James resting

events.name: LA Clippers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — When the Golden State Warriors stopped playing the stingy defense that has carried them recently, Paul George and Norman Powell found every opening.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell, George lead Clippers back from 12 down in fourth to beat Curry, Warriors 130-125
